cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new construction of LDPC codes and discusses their performance in terms of error correction. This is a key area of research in information theory.
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of a Quasi-Cyclic algorithm to optimize the storage of parity-check matrices in decoders. This is a topic that falls under the umbrella of data structures and algorithms.
3. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper presents a hardware model of the parity-check storage units designed for Xilinx FPGA. This falls under the category of hardware architecture.
4. cs.ET (Embedded Systems) - The use of FPGA for hardware implementation of the proposed LDPC codes is relevant to the field of embedded systems.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the processing speed improvement achieved by the proposed LDPC codes. This falls under the category of systems and control.
